// Hybrid LLM + Classical ML — heterogeneous expert composition
// CoE (2024): https://arxiv.org/pdf/2412.01868
// Marcus & Belle, AAAI 2025: neural generation + symbolic/classical ML scoring
//
// Pattern: LLMAnalyst extracts structured quality signals from text →
// ExtractFeatures (kind: json_extract) bridges the LLM output into typed numeric
// context keys → Scorer (kind: onnx) runs a trained ML model for calibrated
// numeric scoring → LLMInterpreter explains the score in plain language.
//
// This is the Composition of Experts (CoE) pattern applied to heterogeneous
// expert types: not all-LLM, but LLM + classical ML. The pipeline treats an
// ONNX model as a first-class expert — declared in the mission file, resolved
// by the runtime.
//
// SETUP: Before running, generate the ONNX model:
//   pip install scikit-learn skl2onnx numpy
//   python generate_model.py
//
// Usage: forge run --mission HybridLLMML

let content = "New feature shipped: CSV export for user data. Completes the core data portability requirement. Implementation was straightforward and code is clean. JSON export may be added later but is not required."

mission HybridLLMML(content) = {
    LLMAnalyst
    -> ExtractFeatures
    -> Scorer
    -> LLMInterpreter
}

output(HybridLLMML)
